<subSubSection id="07AF96B5FFC3FFEDF7F06220FC65CCA1" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4F0AC53EFFC3FFEDF7F06220FC65CCA1" blockId="39.[675,1212,564,1002]" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">
Represented by 3 fruiting collections from the Montagne d’Ambre. Leaves are 4-7 × 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFC3FFEDF1686240FB7CCD24" box="[1085,1207,596,623]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" unit="cm" value="2.0" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.5">1.5-2.5 cm</quantity>
, glabrous, petioles to 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFC3FFEDF6D76260FC09CDC5" box="[898,962,628,654]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
long, domatia lacking. Terminal buds are slender and appressed pubescent. Fruits are 3 × 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFC3FFEDF67862A7FCBCCD85" box="[813,887,691,718]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" unit="cm" value="1.5">1.5 cm</quantity>
, cupules shallow, bowl-shaped, 
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFC3FFEDF7F662C7FD78CDA7" box="[675,691,723,748]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">c.</emphasis>
<quantity id="884D68DBFFC3FFEDF7EF62C6FCC9CDA6" box="[698,770,722,749]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" unit="cm" value="1.5">1.5 cm</quantity>
across and 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFC3FFEDF62362C7FC7ECDA6" box="[886,949,723,749]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
high. The black fruits are almost fully exposed on the red cupule; this color combination suggests the fruits were mature. It differs mainly from 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFC3FFEDF6286326FC37CC07" authorityName="Kosterm. Kostermans" authorityYear="1957" baseAuthorityName="Danguy" box="[893,1020,818,844]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosa">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFC3FFEDF6286326FC37CC07" box="[893,1020,818,844]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">O. racemosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the large fruits and shallow, wide cupules. Flowers are not known. The three collections are 
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFC3FFEDF6FD6365FD39CCE0" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">Andrianantoanina &amp; Rocsce 365</emphasis>
(MO, P), 
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFC3FFEDF63E6385FB9BCCE0" box="[875,1104,913,939]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">Malcomber et al. 982</emphasis>
(MO, P) and 
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFC3FFEDF78663A4FC44CC80" box="[723,911,944,971]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">Schatz et al. 1497</emphasis>
(MO, P) and were made in September and October.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
